}# NarrativeOS - Creative Development Environment

## Overview

NarrativeOS is a full-stack web application designed as a VS Code-inspired development environment specifically tailored for creative professionals. The platform serves as a unified workspace for writers, directors, producers, and other creative professionals, featuring collaborative editing capabilities, AI integration points, and industry-standard formatting tools. Built with React/TypeScript frontend and Express.js backend, it provides real-time collaboration features, multiple editing modules (story writing, screenplay, storyboard), and intelligent AI orchestration for creative workflows.

## User Preferences

Preferred communication style: Simple, everyday language.

## System Architecture

### Frontend Architecture
- **Framework**: React 18 with TypeScript, using Vite as the build tool
- **UI Library**: Radix UI components with shadcn/ui styling system for consistent, accessible interfaces
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom design tokens optimized for dark-mode creative workflows
- **State Management**: React Context API for shared state, with TanStack Query for server state management
- **Routing**: Wouter for lightweight client-side routing
- **Design System**: VS Code-inspired interface with Notion-like creative workspace elements, featuring dark theme optimization

### Component Architecture
- **Modular Components**: Self-contained components for ActivityBar, FileExplorer, CodeEditor, PreviewPane, and StatusBar
- **Real-time Collaboration**: Socket.IO integration planned for live editing and presence indicators
- **Resizable Panes**: Custom ResizablePanes component for flexible workspace layouts
- **Theme System**: Comprehensive dark/light theme support with CSS custom properties

### Backend Architecture
- **Framework**: Express.js with TypeScript for type-safe server development
- **API Design**: RESTful API structure with placeholder routes for future creative modules
- **Development Setup**: Hot module replacement via Vite integration for seamless development experience
- **Error Handling**: Centralized error handling middleware with structured error responses

### Data Storage Solutions
- **ORM**: Drizzle ORM for type-safe database operations with PostgreSQL
- **Database**: PostgreSQL configured via Neon serverless (environment-based configuration)
- **Schema Management**: Drizzle migrations with shared schema definitions
- **Development Storage**: In-memory storage implementation for rapid prototyping

### Authentication and Authorization
- **Planned Implementation**: Multi-user system with role-based access (Writer, Director, Producer, VFX Artist, General Creative)
- **Authentication Methods**: Email/password with Google OAuth integration planned
- **Session Management**: Express sessions with PostgreSQL session store (connect-pg-simple)

### AI Integration Architecture
- **Orchestration Hub**: Centralized routing system for multiple AI services with cost optimization
- **Service Abstraction**: Placeholder integration points for image generation, video creation, text enhancement, and cinematic effects
- **Quality Control**: Built-in quality scoring and usage tracking systems
- **Cost Management**: API rate limiting and usage monitoring

## External Dependencies

### Core Framework Dependencies
- **React Ecosystem**: React 18, React DOM, React Router (Wouter)
- **Build Tools**: Vite with TypeScript support, ESBuild for production builds
- **Development Tools**: TSX for TypeScript execution, various Vite plugins for enhanced development

### UI and Styling
- **Component Library**: Radix UI primitives for accessible, unstyled components
- **Styling Framework**: Tailwind CSS with PostCSS processing
- **Design Tokens**: shadcn/ui configuration for consistent component styling
- **Icons**: Lucide React for comprehensive icon library

### State Management and Data Fetching
- **Server State**: TanStack React Query for caching and synchronization
- **Form Handling**: React Hook Form with Zod resolvers for validation
- **Real-time Features**: Socket.IO (planned integration for collaborative features)

### Database and ORM
- **Database Provider**: Neon Database (PostgreSQL serverless)
- **ORM**: Drizzle ORM with Drizzle Kit for migrations
- **Schema Validation**: Drizzle-Zod for runtime type validation
- **Session Storage**: connect-pg-simple for PostgreSQL-backed sessions

### Planned AI Service Integrations
- **Image Generation**: DALL-E 3, Midjourney, Stable Diffusion APIs
- **Video Generation**: RunwayML, Pika Labs, Stable Video APIs  
- **Image Editing**: Photoshop API, Canva API, Remove.bg
- **Text Enhancement**: Claude 3.5 Sonnet, GPT-4, Gemini Pro
- **Cinematic Effects**: After Effects scripting, LUT processing APIs

### Development and Deployment
- **Runtime Environment**: Node.js with ES modules
- **Development Platform**: Replit-optimized with cartographer plugin
- **Error Monitoring**: Runtime error overlay for development
- **Type Checking**: TypeScript strict mode with comprehensive type coverageimport type { Config } from "tailwindcss";
