🏗️ 1. Story Structures &amp; Plot Models
Help users plan strong narrative arcs and pacing:
            * The Hero’s Journey (Joseph Campbell)
 Summary of the 12-stage monomyth structure. Excellent for epic, fantasy, or adventure stories.
KB File: heros_journey_summary.pdf
            * Save the Cat! Beat Sheet (Blake Snyder)
 A 15-beat formula for commercial storytelling and screenwriting.
KB File: save_the_cat_beat_sheet.pdf
            * Three-Act Structure
 Classic beginning-middle-end storytelling. Use it across any genre.
KB File: three_act_structure_guide.pdf
            * The Snowflake Method
 A detailed step-by-step guide to expand a single sentence into a full novel.
KB File: snowflake_method_outline.pdf
            * Story Spine (Pixar)
 Simple format perfect for short stories and beginners. (“Once upon a time…”).
KB File: pixar_story_spine_template.md
            * Dan Harmon’s Story Circle
 Modern, simplified Hero’s Journey adapted for film/TV.
